<subSubSection id="57B7F7FB5168C75078A6FD24FBA5FC97" pageId="5" pageNumber="243" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="1F12A4705168C75078A6FD24FBA5FC97" blockId="5.[151,1437,699,1230]" pageId="5" pageNumber="243">
<emphasis id="2DD978625168C75078A6FD24FECAFD24" bold="true" box="[151,274,699,725]" pageId="5" pageNumber="243">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
This species can be distinguished from other 
<taxonomicName id="D8ADDFF35168C7507B2EFD24FC20FD24" box="[799,1016,699,725]" pageId="5" pageNumber="243">
<emphasis id="2DD978625168C7507B2EFD24FC47FD24" box="[799,927,699,725]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="243">Diplonevra</emphasis>
species
</taxonomicName>
by the combination of the following characteristics: inner face of hind trochanter with one stout seta; ventrobasal area of inner face of hind femur highly sclerotized proximally, with two short setae; hind tibia with three longitudinal setal palisades and one anterodorsal bristle before apical quarter; wing vein M 
<subScript id="8329A6355168C7507A55FCA5FDB4FCB9" attach="left" box="[612,620,826,840]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="243">1</subScript>
straight; male abdominal tergites 2–5 dark brown and venter pale yellow; female abdominal tergites 1, 5 and venter pale yellow (modified from 
<bibRefCitation id="7B3CD9815168C7507B9BFCD4FBA9FC97" author="Liu, G. C. &amp; Yang, M." box="[938,1137,843,870]" pageId="5" pageNumber="243" pagination="31 - 51" refId="ref18651" refString="Liu, G. C. &amp; Yang, M. (2016) A taxonomic revision of the genus Diplonevra Lioy (Diptera: Phoridae) from China. Zootaxa, 4205 (1), 31 - 51. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 4205.1.3" type="journal article" year="2016">Liu &amp; Yang 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="57B7F7FB5168C75078F6FCEFFC5BFB5B" pageId="5" pageNumber="243" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="1F12A4705168C75078F6FCEFFC5BFB5B" blockId="5.[151,1437,699,1230]" pageId="5" pageNumber="243">
<emphasis id="2DD978625168C75078F6FCEFFEE3FC7B" bold="true" box="[199,315,880,906]" pageId="5" pageNumber="243">Remarks.</emphasis>
This species is mainly distributed in southeastern Asia. The Korean distribution of the species has been recorded in checklists only (ZSK 1968; ESK &amp; KSAE 1994; 
<bibRefCitation id="7B3CD9815168C7507B48FC0CFBF7FC5F" author="Paek, M. K. &amp; Hwang, J. M. &amp; Jung, K. S. &amp; Kim, T. W. &amp; Kim, M. C. &amp; Lee, Y. J. &amp; Cho, Y. B. &amp; Park, S. W. &amp; Lee, H. S. &amp; Ku, D. S." box="[889,1071,915,942]" pageId="5" pageNumber="243" refId="ref18959" refString="Paek, M. K., Hwang, J. M., Jung, K. S., Kim, T. W., Kim, M. C., Lee, Y. J., Cho, Y. B., Park, S. W., Lee, H. S. &amp; Ku, D. S. (2010) Checklist of Korean insects. Nature and Ecology, Academic Series 2. Nature and Ecology, Seoul, 598 pp. [in Korean]" type="book" year="2010">
Paek 
<emphasis id="2DD978625168C7507B87FC0BFC35FC5C" box="[950,1005,915,941]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="243">et al.</emphasis>
2010
</bibRefCitation>
; NIBR 2019). Although we were unable to examine the specimens of this species, photographs of a female specimen were available for proper identification of the species based on overall appearance (wing vein M 
<subScript id="8329A6355168C7507B48FC71FC59FC0D" attach="left" box="[889,897,1006,1020]" fontSize="6" pageId="5" pageNumber="243">1</subScript>
straight, abdominal tergites 1 and 5 pale yellow, abdominal tergites 2–4 dark brown, and abdominal venter pale yellow), which were consistent with the features of 
<taxonomicName id="D8ADDFF35168C75078A6FBBBFEF0FBCC" authorityName=": Schmitz" authorityYear="1929" box="[151,296,1059,1085]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Diploneura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="bifasciata">
<emphasis id="2DD978625168C75078A6FBBBFEF0FBCC" box="[151,296,1059,1085]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="243">D. bifasciata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. The photographs were available from two research reports (
<bibRefCitation id="7B3CD9815168C7507BE6FBBBFB47FBCF" author="Kwon, T. S. &amp; Lee, C. M. &amp; Jie, O. Y. &amp; Kim, S. S. &amp; Park, G. E. &amp; Lim, J. H." box="[983,1183,1059,1086]" pageId="5" pageNumber="243" refId="ref18409" refString="Kwon, T. S., Lee, C. M., Jie, O. Y., Kim, S. S., Park, G. E. &amp; Lim, J. H. (2015) Change of Korean fly (Diptera) abundance according to climate warming. Research Note 608, National Institute of Forest Science, Seoul, 669 pp. [in Korean]" type="book" year="2015">
Kwon 
<emphasis id="2DD978625168C7507C15FBBBFB8EFBCC" box="[1060,1110,1059,1085]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="243">et al</emphasis>
. 2015
</bibRefCitation>
; 
<bibRefCitation id="7B3CD9815168C7507C9AFBBBFB30FBCF" author="Kwon, T. S. &amp; Jie, O. Y. &amp; Lee, C. M. &amp; Kim, S. S. &amp; Park, G. E." box="[1195,1256,1060,1086]" pageId="5" pageNumber="243" refId="ref18485" refString="Kwon, T. S., Jie, O. Y., Lee, C. M., Kim, S. S. &amp; Park, G. E. (2018) Distribution (2006 - 2009) of forest flies (Phoridae, Lauxaniidae, Empididae, and Dolichopodidae) and climate change prediction. National Institute of Forest Science, Seoul, 158 pp. [in Korean]" type="book" year="2018">2018</bibRefCitation>
). The collection site of the specimen was provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="7B3CD9815168C7507A75FBD7FCC5FB93" author="Kwon, T. S. &amp; Lee, C. M. &amp; Jie, O. Y. &amp; Kim, S. S. &amp; Park, G. E. &amp; Lim, J. H." box="[580,797,1095,1122]" pageId="5" pageNumber="243" refId="ref18409" refString="Kwon, T. S., Lee, C. M., Jie, O. Y., Kim, S. S., Park, G. E. &amp; Lim, J. H. (2015) Change of Korean fly (Diptera) abundance according to climate warming. Research Note 608, National Institute of Forest Science, Seoul, 669 pp. [in Korean]" type="book" year="2015">
Kwon 
<emphasis id="2DD978625168C7507AA0FBD7FD1BFB90" box="[657,707,1095,1121]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="243">et al</emphasis>
. (2015)
</bibRefCitation>
(
<collectingCountry id="67BAE4E05168C7507B1DFBD8FC18FB93" box="[812,960,1095,1122]" name="South Korea" pageId="5" pageNumber="243">South Korea</collectingCountry>
: 
<collectingRegion id="DD696A925168C7507BFAFBD8FBBDFB90" box="[971,1125,1095,1121]" country="South Korea" name="Jeonnam" pageId="5" pageNumber="243">Jeollanam-do</collectingRegion>
, Naju-si, Daeho-dong, near Dongsin University, 
<geoCoordinate id="7A99C2B75168C75079B0FBF2FDC6FB79" box="[385,542,1133,1160]" degrees="35" direction="north" minutes="02" orientation="latitude" pageId="5" pageNumber="243" precision="1" seconds="54.8" value="35.048553">35°02′54.8″N</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="7A99C2B75168C7507A1AFBF2FD0CFB79" box="[555,724,1133,1160]" degrees="126" direction="east" minutes="42" orientation="longitude" pageId="5" pageNumber="243" precision="1" seconds="59.2" value="126.71644">126°42′59.2″E</geoCoordinate>
), but the voucher specimen is missing. The specimen was misidentified as 
<taxonomicName id="D8ADDFF35168C7507919FB0FFE1AFB58" authorityName=": Schmitz" authorityYear="1927" box="[296,450,1167,1193]" class="Insecta" family="Phoridae" genus="Diploneura" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="243" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="abbreviata">
<emphasis id="2DD978625168C7507919FB0FFE1AFB58" box="[296,450,1167,1193]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="243">D. abbreviata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in a later report (
<bibRefCitation id="7B3CD9815168C7507AB5FB0FFCAEFB5B" author="Kwon, T. S. &amp; Jie, O. Y. &amp; Lee, C. M. &amp; Kim, S. S. &amp; Park, G. E." box="[644,886,1167,1194]" pageId="5" pageNumber="243" refId="ref18485" refString="Kwon, T. S., Jie, O. Y., Lee, C. M., Kim, S. S. &amp; Park, G. E. (2018) Distribution (2006 - 2009) of forest flies (Phoridae, Lauxaniidae, Empididae, and Dolichopodidae) and climate change prediction. National Institute of Forest Science, Seoul, 158 pp. [in Korean]" type="book" year="2018">
Kwon 
<emphasis id="2DD978625168C7507AE0FB0FFCDAFB58" box="[721,770,1167,1193]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="243">et al</emphasis>
. 2018: 61
</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
